title: Tin Cans over Pennsylvania
name: Tin Cans over Pennsylvania
description:
A Map by Rubaccaquon

Tin Cans Over Pennsylvania is an oral charting of simultaneous meanderings through the  booming metropli of Pennsylvania. The places on this map illustrate a walk through the cities of Pittsburgh and Philadelphia. The second part of this project is a recorded coversation that follows this walk, noting architecture, commerce, crowds, and coincidences. The conversation will be played through a tin can telephone line stretched over a six foot map of the state of Pennsylvania. It will be installed at VersionFest06 in Chicago.
